ver, it seems there's no need for reflection in the test.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring security metadata requirements**\\n\\nI need to consider native security metadata for domain class fields, possibly through an agent. I’ll utilize simple public bean fields. I wonder if the native image can reflect user test classes while the agent collects information? It seems like the user-code-filter only includes com.thoughtworks.xstream, which excludes any test classes. Should there be conditional metadata specifically for the test code? Hmm, I need to understand how the agent filters user code to include the library. There's a lot to consider!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fpIEN21Sa8m7tNGz8fw7FpQh|fc_08a03acc398fda990169f0085b01a08195ad8e6ac0010f4fa5", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/c/forge2/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/main/extracted/com/thoughtworks/xstream/XStream.java", "offset": 735, "limit": 100}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 682, "output": 1310, "cacheRead": 13312, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 15304, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777338435930, "responseId": "resp_08a03acc398fda990169f0084449008195b3983f3f426bc4ee"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_fpIEN21Sa8m7tNGz8fw7FpQh|fc_08a03acc398fda990169f0085b01a08195ad8e6ac0010f4fa5", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "        Class type = JVM.loadClassForName(className);\n        if (type != null) {\n            denyTypeHierarchy(type);\n        }\n    }\n\n    /**\n     * Setup the security framework of a XStream instance.\n     * <p>\n     * This method was a pure helper method for XStream 1.4.10 to 1.4.17.  It initialized an XStream instance with a\n     * whitelist of well-known and simply types of the Java